               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Mǝʿrāf, The Common of the Office (fols. 3ra-63vb)
 I-1) Wāzemā,
                     The Office of Vigils (fols. 3ra-8ra)
 I-2) Mawaddǝs, The Sunday Office
                     (fols. 8ra-18rb)
 I-3) ʾAnqaṣa bǝrhān “Gate of Light” (fols.
                     18rb-20rb)
 I-4) Sǝbḥāta nagh, The Office of Matins (fols. 20rb-25rb)
                     I-5) Za-mawāʿǝla ʾaṣwām, The Office for Lent (fols. 25rb-43vb)
 I-6)
                     ʾArǝʾstä mǝhǝlla [za-Dāwit], Rogation (fols. 43vb-48va)
 I-7) Qāla barakat
                     za-Yāred, Blessing of Yāred (fols. 48va-49vb)
 I-8) Za-yǝnaggǝś za-ʾabuna
                     Yāred, Supplications of Yāred (fols. 50ra-51vb)
 I-9) Kǝśtat za-ʾaryām, The
                     festive Office (fols. 52ra-58va)
 I-10) Mastabqʷǝʿ, Supplications (fols.
                     58va-62rb)
 I-11) Ṣalota kidān za-śalastu gizeyāt “Covenant Prayer of the
                     Three Hours” (fols. 62rb-63vb).</summary>
