                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; titles of Texts I-1 to I-11; names of
                           supplications, antiphons and chants (often their initial letters), and
                           their abbreviations (e.g., mastabqʷǝʿ, mǝqnāy, mǝlṭān, mazmur, salām,
                           mǝhǝla, ʾarǝʾst); initial words of supplications and prayers in Text
                           I-10; names of feasts and other occasions; interlinear musical signs
                           (e.g., fols. 44rab-45ra, 49vb); directives for the ministers; names of
                           the categories of melody and their abbreviations (ʿǝzl, gǝʿǝz, ʾararay);
                           elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals and/or their
                           elements.
 Two lines (alternating with a black line) on the incipit
                           page; two lines (alternating with a black line) of the incipit of Texts
                           I-2, I-5 and I-6; two lines of the incipit of Texts I-3 and I-7.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="3ra" to="49vb">3ra-49vb</locus>, 52ra-63rb; on <locus from="40v" to="41v">40v-41v</locus> the handwriting becomes conspicuously right-sloping.
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: <locus from="50ra" to="51vb">50ra-51vb</locus>; the handwriting is
                        right-sloping.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#49vb">49vb</locus> (explicit of Text I-7) three short and
                        simple ornamental bands; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#62rb">62rb</locus> (explicit of Text I-10): simple,
                        uncoloured ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- The liturgical period, for which Text I-1 is used,
                              is indicated in the upper margin of <locus target="#3va">fol.
                                 3va</locus> (in red): በሰናብት፡ ወበዓላት. - Daily readings are indicated
                              by the names of the days of the week written in the upper margin, in a
                              secondary hand (?): ዘሠኑይ: <locus target="#26ra">fol. 26ra</locus>
                              ዘሠሉስ: <locus target="#29ra">fol. 29ra</locus> ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#30vb">fol. 30vb</locus> ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#32rb">fol.
                                 32rb</locus> ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#34ra">fol. 34ra</locus> ዘቀዳሚት:
                                 <locus target="#35va">fol. 35va</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where the omissions, written in the margins, belong, in the main hand: fols. 3vb l.13, 5va l.12, 8rb l.22, 9rb l.2, 33vb l.10, 36vb l.23, 49vb l.19. - Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of a cross or two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where the omissions, written in the margins, belong, in secondary hands: fols. 3rb l.19, 4ra l.4, 5rb l.24, 10vb l.14, 21va l.19, 22ra l.5, 38vb l.23, 40ra l.5. - Omitted words and passages written in the margins: fols. 3rb, 3va, 4ra, 6vb, 7rb, 8va, 9ra, 9va, 11rb, 12va, 14ra, 15ra, 19rb, 20rb, 22vb, 23rb, 24va, 26va, 30rb, 30va, 31rb, 31vb, 32rb, 38rab, 39ra, 40rb, 40vab, 41ra, 43rb, 44rb, 50rb, 51ra, 51va, 57vab, 60r, 61rab, 63v. - Erasures: fols. 8rb, 12vb. - Erasures marked with thin lines: fols. 19rb, 54ra. - A sign, in the shape of a cross with a circle at the ends of the vertical arm, is written in the side margins: <locus target="#3v">fol.  3v</locus>. - A few lines on <locus target="#49vb">fol.  49vb</locus> are written in a smaller script. - Lack of rubrication on fols. 53vb-54vb, 62ra-63vb. - Minor note, in Amharic and Gǝʿǝz: <locus target="#55va">fol.  55va</locus> (in the bottom margin). - Pen trial: fols. 1v, 2r, 29v, 34vb, 45r, 59v. - Scribbles, writing exercises, doodles: fols. 1v, 2r, 23vb, 33vb, 34ra, 60r, 63v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
